Hurricane Harbor Water Park is a part of Six Flags New England! The bonus here is that you can not only enjoy the attractions of the Water Park but if your heart desire's, you can also walk over and explore the rest of Six Flags! This makes for a great couple of days at Six Flags!
Hurricane Harbor Water Park is ready to pack in a day of fun for all water enthusiasts from the little ones to the thrill seekers. Be sure to check out attractions like the Cannonball Falls as you catapult yourself down an incredibly vertical tube, or the Bonzai Pipelines where you can be sent down a 257 foot 40 mph chute! Or grab three other friends to climb aboard a raft on the Geronimo and Zooma Falls where full action slides will provide a thrilling ride down to the bottom where you are welcomed in to a luxurious pool. Don't give the Tornado a miss either. This is a tunnel where guests can raft down an enormous funnel that propels you down 132 feet!
For more gentle fun, check out Commotion Ocean - a 500,000 gallon wave pool with true to form tides and waves, Monsoon Lagoon where you can lounge and relax, or the Kiddie Octopus designed for children to enjoy a water play structure. Kids too will enjoy Splash Island where they get their very own lazy river and wave pool.

